  "uuid": "108225aff748fcd270409e2333df22bf",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Ducting Project Manager",
  "description": "<h2>Ducting Project Manager (HVAC / Ventilation)</h2><h3>Job Scope / Responsibilities</h3><p><strong>1. Project Planning & Coordination</strong></p><ul><li><p>Plan, manage, and oversee ducting works for HVAC and ventilation projects</p></li><li><p>Define project scope, timelines, manpower requirements, and budgets</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with consultants, main contractors, and clients on project requirements</p></li></ul><p><strong>2. Site Management & Supervision</strong></p><ul><li><p>Supervise site works including duct fabrication, installation, insulation, and testing</p></li><li><p>Ensure works are carried out according to approved drawings, specifications, and schedules</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with other trades (ACMV, electrical, fire protection, architectural)</p></li></ul><p><strong>3. Technical & Drawing Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Review and interpret construction drawings, shop drawings, and specifications</p></li><li><p>Coordinate preparation and submission of shop drawings and method statements</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with BCA, SCDF, and relevant Singapore standards</p></li></ul><p><strong>4. Quality, Safety & Compliance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure ducting works meet quality standards and project specifications</p></li><li><p>Enforce workplace safety, risk assessments, and safe work procedures</p></li><li><p>Conduct site inspections and rectify non-conformances</p></li></ul><p><strong>5. Progress, Cost & Resource Control</strong></p><ul><li><p>Monitor project progress and ensure timely completion</p></li><li><p>Manage manpower, subcontractors, and material procurement</p></li><li><p>Control project costs and variations related to ducting works</p></li></ul><p><strong>6. Stakeholder & Communication Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Liaise with clients, consultants, main contractors, and authorities</p></li><li><p>Attend site meetings, coordination meetings, and progress reviews</p></li><li><p>Prepare progress reports, method statements, and project documentation</p></li></ul><p><strong>7. Testing, Commissioning & Handover</strong></p><ul><li><p>Coordinate testing, commissioning, and inspections for ducting systems</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper handover documentation including as-built drawings</p></li><li><p>Close out defects and outstanding works</p></li></ul><h2>Job Requirements / Qualifications</h2><h3>Education & Certification</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in <strong>Mechanical Engineering, Building Services, or related field</strong></p></li><li><p>Relevant safety certifications (e.g. <strong>WSH, BCA Safety Pass</strong>) preferred</p></li></ul><h3>Experience</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>3–5 years of experience</strong> in ducting / HVAC project management</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience in <strong>ACMV ducting fabrication and installation</strong></p></li><li><p>Experience managing subcontractors and site teams</p></li></ul>",
